<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910725-0158</DOCNO><DOCID>910725-0158.</DOCID><HL>   Who's News:   Amax Restructures   Its Top Management   To Reflect Diversity</HL><DATE>07/25/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   AMX WNEWS</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)ENERGY (ENE)</MS><IN>ALUMINUM (ALU)COAL PRODUCERS (COA)ALL NON-FERROUS METALS (NFR)OIL-INTEGRATED MAJORS (OIL)PETROLEUM (PET)</IN><NS>PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)PETROLEUM MARKET (PET)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   NEW YORK -- Amax Inc. said it reorganized its topmanagement to reflect the company's evolution from a majoraluminum producer to a &quot;more balanced&quot; company with energyand aluminum businesses.   Paul Drack, formerly president of the company's AlumaxInc. unit, was named president and chief operating officer, anew position. He succeeds Chairman and Chief ExecutiveOfficer Allen Born as president. Mr. Born has held all threeposts since he was named chairman in 1988. The move &quot;willcentralize responsibility for all operating businesses in onesenior corporate executive,&quot; Amax said.</LP><TEXT>   In addition, the company formed a new unit, Amax EnergyInc., which combines Amax's coal, oil and gas businesses, andnamed Thomas A. McKeever, formerly executive vice presidentof the parent company, as president and chief executiveofficer of the new unit. He will be responsible for Amax Oilandamp; Gas Inc. and Amax Coal Industries Inc.   V. Bond Evans, formerly executive vice president ofAlumax, was named to succeed Mr. Drack as president of thealuminum unit. Mr. Evans; Mr. McKeever; Stephen Johnson,president of Climax Metals Co.; and Timothy Haddon, presidentof Amax Gold Inc.; will report to Mr. Drack.   Mr. Born said the changes are part of the company'sstrategy to balance its businesses, which include goldmining, energy production and aluminum production. Higherenergy prices, which depress margins in the aluminumbusiness, can raise profits in the company's energybusinesses, Mr. Born said. The company purchased LaddPetroleum last year, raising its natural gas reserves toabout one trillion cubic feet. It also purchased CanneltonHolding Co. from Algoma Steel Corp. in December, adding thatcompany's low-sulfur Eastern coal to its reserves.</TEXT></DOC>